## 🏛️ Overview

**Donald Bogle** is an award-winning film historian, author, and professor specializing in **African American representation in Hollywood**. His works critically examine the portrayal of Black characters in film and television, exposing racial stereotypes while highlighting the contributions of Black actors and filmmakers.

Bogle is regarded as **one of the foremost authorities on Black cinema**, providing groundbreaking analysis of how Hollywood has historically depicted Black people and how these portrayals have evolved over time.

