## 🌍 Impact on Africana Studies

Donald Bogle’s work is **essential to Africana Studies**, as it critically examines **Hollywood’s role in shaping racial narratives** and **Black identity** in media. His books have influenced:

✔️ **Media Studies & Film Criticism** – Providing analytical tools to assess racial imagery.  
✔️ **Civil Rights & Representation** – Connecting Hollywood portrayals to broader social struggles.  
✔️ **Black Filmmaking & Storytelling** – Elevating and preserving Black cinematic history.

